ritten, published and received in England as compared to mainland Europe, and explores the works of major (Shakespeare, Sidney, Spenser) and minor (Barnes, Harvey) poets alike. Reflecting on current editorial practices, it also provides the first modern edition of an early seventeenth-century Elizabethan miscellany including sonnets presumably by Sidney and Spenser.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish poetryyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 0aSonnets, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 4aShakespeare 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aBook history.  aEarly Modern poetry.  aPetrarchism.  aPoetic collections.  aReception.  aSonnet.  aTextual criticism.1 aChaghafi, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChiari, Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoatalen, Guillaume, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEastman, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGazzard, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGirotto, Carlo Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, William John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonferran, Jean-Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSansonetti, Laetitia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSansonetti, Laetitia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStamatakis, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVuillemin, Rémi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVuillemin, Rémi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZanin, 